Wonder Woman is directed by Patty Jenkins who’s last movie 'Monster', earned Charlize Theron an Oscar. NEW YORK - Actress Gal Gadot says the_ Wonder Woman _movie has a message for both women and men to heed. Gadot stars as the title character in the movie, which is the first big studio superhero film to be directed by a woman, and opens in cinemas today. Gadot says the film's message of love and compassion is important. “These are values that are well needed, especially nowadays and they’re very, very relevant.” She believes the film isn't just for women. “Men and boys can enjoy this movie as well. It’s such a universal movie.” Wonder Woman is directed by Patty Jenkins whose last movie Monster, earned Charlize Theron an Oscar.